    <text id="A8525T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Fredrick Burns asks John H. McCue if he knows of a teaching position for Burns'
                    son.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">J. H. McCue Esq.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1859-08-05"><abbr expan="August">Aug.</abbr> 5<hi rend="super">th</hi> '59</date>
                        <name type="place">Waynesboro</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have a Son who wishes a situation as School Teacher and I thought perhaps you
                    might know of a situation in your region of country that would suit him
                    &amp; that he would suit. He has had some little experience in teaching
                    previous to his going to College. He has just returned from Emory &amp;
                    Henry College &amp; has testimonials as to his standing while at College
                    &amp; also his qualifications.</p>

                <p>He is prepared to teach the usual English branches, <abbr expan="Natural"
                    >Nat.</abbr> Philosophy, Arithmetic, Algebra, Geometry, Surveying, Plane
                    &amp; Spherical Trigonometry &amp; Latin.</p>

                <p>If you know of a situation &amp; will let him know of it at your earliest
                    convenience you will confer a <orig reg="favor">favour</orig> which will be
                    gladly reciprocated should an opportunity occur.</p>

                <p>Please excuse the liberty I have taken in troubling you with this</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Most Respectfully</salute>
                    <signed>F. Burns</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">P. S. <orig reg="Anyone">Any one</orig> wishing to know
                        the moral character &amp; standing of my son are <orig reg="referred"
                            >refered</orig> to <abbr expan="Captain">Cap<hi rend="super"
                        >t</hi></abbr> B. M. Ellis, <abbr expan="William">W<hi rend="super"
                        >m</hi></abbr> Withrow James Irvine, Mr. Fishburn &amp; Mr King. You can
                        address W. H. Burns or myself at <orig reg="Waynesboro"
                        >Waynesboro'</orig><lb/>Yours ---<lb/>F. B.</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
